# User Interface Components

The Random Beep extension has three main UI components: Popup, Options page, and Statistics page.

## Popup Interface

The popup is the main user interaction point:

- [popup/popup.html](mdc:popup/popup.html): HTML structure
- [popup/popup.js](mdc:popup/popup.js): UI logic 
- [popup/popup.css](mdc:popup/popup.css): Styling

The popup provides:
- Current session status
- Timer display
- Control buttons (Start, Pause, Reset)
- Daily statistics summary
- Link to full statistics page

## Options Page

The options page allows the user to customize the extension:

- [options/options.html](mdc:options/options.html): HTML structure
- [options/options.js](mdc:options/options.js): Settings logic
- [options/options.css](mdc:options/options.css): Styling

It manages:
- Timer duration settings
- Break frequency settings
- Notification preferences
- Theme customization

## Statistics Page

The statistics page visualizes the user's focus data:

- [statistics/statistics.html](mdc:statistics/statistics.html): HTML structure
- [statistics/statistics.js](mdc:statistics/statistics.js): Data visualization
- [statistics/statistics.css](mdc:statistics/statistics.css): Styling

Features:
- Daily focus time charts
- Break distribution visualization
- Focus metrics display
- Data export options

## Common UI Utilities

Shared UI utilities can be found in:
- [utils/dom-utils.js](mdc:utils/dom-utils.js): DOM manipulation utilities
- [utils/time-utils.js](mdc:utils/time-utils.js): Time formatting and calculations
